<subSubSection id="11E3DCD4FFB4FFD8FF3EFC91FD3DFC35" pageId="11" pageNumber="280" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="59468F5FFFB4FFD8FF3EFC91FD3DFC35" blockId="11.[113,765,823,943]" pageId="11" pageNumber="280">
<emphasis id="6B8D534DFFB4FFD8FF3EFC91FD22FCD5" box="[151,738,823,847]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="280">
Distribution and ecology. – 
<taxonomicName id="9EF9F4DCFFB4FFD8FE6BFC91FD22FCD5" authorityName="Buerki, Callm., Munzinger &amp; Lowry" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Buerki, Callm., Munzinger &amp; Lowry" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[450,738,823,847]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Lepidocupania" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="11" pageNumber="280" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tontoutensis">Lepidocupania tontoutensis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is endemic to Grande Terre, where it is restricted to the Tontouta River valley. It is found in maquis vegetation on serpentine substrate, mostly alluvium, between 20 and 
<quantity id="9E0122BAFFB4FFD8FDBBFC31FD94FC34" box="[530,596,919,943]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="280" unit="m" value="100.0">100 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation id="3D68F2AEFFB4FFD8FDCAFC31FD32FC35" author="ADEMA, F." box="[611,754,919,943]" pageId="11" pageNumber="280" refId="ref11451" refString="ADEMA, F. (1991). Cupaniopsis Radlk. (Sapindaceae): a monograph. Leiden Bot. Ser. 15." type="book" year="1991">ADEMA, 1991</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="11E3DCD4FFB4FFD8FF3EFC7EFDBCF934" pageId="11" pageNumber="280" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="59468F5FFFB4FFD8FF3EFC7EFDB6FBF5" blockId="11.[113,764,983,1711]" pageId="11" pageNumber="280">
<emphasis id="6B8D534DFFB4FFD8FF3EFC7EFE33FC75" box="[151,499,983,1007]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="280">
Notes. – 
<taxonomicName id="9EF9F4DCFFB4FFD8FF5AFC71FE33FC75" box="[243,499,983,1007]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Cupaniopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="11" pageNumber="280" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tontoutensis">Cupaniopsis tontoutensis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
was described based on 
<emphasis id="6B8D534DFFB4FFD8FFD8FC5EFF24FB95" box="[113,228,1015,1039]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="280">Virot 1448</emphasis>
. Original material at 
<collectionCode id="3FE8179AFFB4FFD8FE7EFC51FE27FB94" box="[471,487,1015,1038]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="11" pageNumber="280" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
is, however, mounted on two sheets, only one of which [
<specimenCode id="095F2724FFB4FFD8FE1FFBB1FDF4FBB5" box="[438,564,1047,1071]" collectionCode="P" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="11" pageNumber="280" type="Herbarium">P00639164</specimenCode>
] bears the name of Guillaumin’s new species in his own hand, along with the word “type”. We regard this specimen as the 
<typeStatus id="864231FDFFB4FFD8FDB8FBF1FDB2FBF5" box="[529,626,1111,1135]" pageId="11" pageNumber="280">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="59468F5FFFB4FFD8FF3EFBD1FDBCF934" blockId="11.[113,764,983,1711]" pageId="11" pageNumber="280">
<taxonomicName id="9EF9F4DCFFB4FFD8FF3EFBD1FE25FB15" authority="Adema" authorityName="Adema" box="[151,485,1143,1167]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Cupaniopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="11" pageNumber="280" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rotundifolia">
<emphasis id="6B8D534DFFB4FFD8FF3EFBD1FE50FB15" box="[151,400,1143,1167]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="280">Cupaniopsis rotundifolia</emphasis>
Adema
</taxonomicName>
was only known from the 
<typeStatus id="864231FDFFB4FFD8FFD8FB31FF5FFB35" box="[113,159,1175,1199]" pageId="11" pageNumber="280">type</typeStatus>
specimen from the Tontouta River valley, with ecological and edaphic preferences similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="9EF9F4DCFFB4FFD8FDEAFB11FD1AFB55" box="[579,730,1207,1231]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Cupaniopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="11" pageNumber="280" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tontoutensis">
<emphasis id="6B8D534DFFB4FFD8FDEAFB11FD1AFB55" box="[579,730,1207,1231]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="280">C. tontoutensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(≡ 
<taxonomicName id="9EF9F4DCFFB4FFD8FFD8FB71FE4CFB75" authorityName="Buerki, Callm., Munzinger &amp; Lowry" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Buerki, Callm., Munzinger &amp; Lowry" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[113,396,1239,1263]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Lepidocupania" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="11" pageNumber="280" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tontoutensis">
<emphasis id="6B8D534DFFB4FFD8FFD8FB71FE4CFB75" box="[113,396,1239,1263]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="280">Lepidocupania tontoutensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), as mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation id="3D68F2AEFFB4FFD8FDC9FB71FF5DFA95" author="ADEMA, F." pageId="11" pageNumber="280" refId="ref11451" refString="ADEMA, F. (1991). Cupaniopsis Radlk. (Sapindaceae): a monograph. Leiden Bot. Ser. 15." type="book" year="1991">ADEMA (1991: 161)</bibRefCitation>
, who wrote: “Probably closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="9EF9F4DCFFB4FFD8FDFEFB51FD0CFA95" box="[599,716,1271,1295]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Lepidocupania" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="11" pageNumber="280" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fruticosa">
<emphasis id="6B8D534DFFB4FFD8FDFEFB51FD0CFA95" box="[599,716,1271,1295]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="280">C. fruticosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="9EF9F4DCFFB4FFD8FFD8FAB1FEC2FAB5" authorityName="Buerki, Callm., Munzinger &amp; Lowry" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Buerki, Callm., Munzinger &amp; Lowry" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[113,258,1303,1327]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Lepidocupania" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="11" pageNumber="280" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tontoutensis">
<emphasis id="6B8D534DFFB4FFD8FFD8FAB1FEC2FAB5" box="[113,258,1303,1327]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="280">C. tontoutensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”. 
<taxonomicName id="9EF9F4DCFFB4FFD8FEBEFAB1FDCCFAB5" box="[279,524,1303,1327]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Cupaniopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="11" pageNumber="280" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tontoutensis">
<emphasis id="6B8D534DFFB4FFD8FEBEFAB1FDCCFAB5" box="[279,524,1303,1327]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="280">Cupaniopsis tontoutensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was said to differ from 
<taxonomicName id="9EF9F4DCFFB4FFD8FFD8FA91FECAFAD5" box="[113,266,1335,1359]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Cupaniopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="11" pageNumber="280" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rotundifolia">
<emphasis id="6B8D534DFFB4FFD8FFD8FA91FECAFAD5" box="[113,266,1335,1359]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="280">C. rotundifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its fewer, wider leaflets with the secondary venation oriented at a wider angle to the midrib, and by the stiff trichomes on the endocarp of its fruits. However, several recent collections made in the lower Tontouta River valley as part of a study of rare species from this area (
<bibRefCitation id="3D68F2AEFFB4FFD8FDEAFA11FD35FA55" author="D'ANGELO, S." box="[579,757,1463,1487]" pageId="11" pageNumber="280" refId="ref11926" refString="D'ANGELO, S. (2017). Ecologie et conservation de trois especes rares et menacees de Nouvelle-Caledonie. Memoire de Master. Universite de Lorraine-UMR ECOFOG, Kourou &amp; IAC, Paita." type="book" year="2017">D’ANGELO, 2017</bibRefCitation>
) show a perfect continuum in leaflet shape (as exemplified by 
<emphasis id="6B8D534DFFB4FFD8FFD8FA51FEB1F995" box="[113,369,1527,1551]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="280">Lannuzel &amp; D'Angelo 49</emphasis>
[MPU312290], 
<emphasis id="6B8D534DFFB4FFD8FDB5FA51FF4BF9B5" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="280">Lannuzel &amp; D'Angelo 34</emphasis>
[MPU091683], and 
<emphasis id="6B8D534DFFB4FFD8FEF6F9B1FD97F9B5" box="[351,599,1559,1583]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="280">Lannuzel &amp; D'Angelo 39</emphasis>
[MPU312292]) and fruits (cf. 
<emphasis id="6B8D534DFFB4FFD8FEA3F991FDD3F9D5" box="[266,531,1591,1615]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="280">Lannuzel &amp; D'Angelo 32</emphasis>
[MPU312293]), with leaves clearly corresponding to 
<taxonomicName id="9EF9F4DCFFB4FFD8FE1FF9FEFD86F9F5" box="[438,582,1624,1647]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Cupaniopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="11" pageNumber="280" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tontoutensis">
<emphasis id="6B8D534DFFB4FFD8FE1FF9FEFD86F9F5" box="[438,582,1624,1647]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="280">L. tontoutensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the presence of stiff trichomes on the endocarp. We have therefore placed 
<taxonomicName id="9EF9F4DCFFB4FFD8FFD8F931FEC7F935" box="[113,263,1687,1711]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Cupaniopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="11" pageNumber="280" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rotundifolia">
<emphasis id="6B8D534DFFB4FFD8FFD8F931FEC7F935" box="[113,263,1687,1711]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="280">C. rotundifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in synonymy under 
<taxonomicName id="9EF9F4DCFFB4FFD8FE4BF93EFDB4F935" box="[482,628,1688,1711]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Cupaniopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="11" pageNumber="280" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tontoutensis">
<emphasis id="6B8D534DFFB4FFD8FE4BF93EFDB4F935" box="[482,628,1688,1711]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="280">L. tontoutensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
